Get the ESA's Climate Change Initiative (CCI) Biomass Data¶

https://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/bf535053562141c6bb7ad831f5998d77/

Due to large data size, we limit our spatial range to the given fire area in Indonesia.

(Ideally we shold look at biomass data pre- and post- fire event which is shorter than a year. But for the time being, I stopped spending too much time in digging dataset with much finner temporal resolution.)

In [ ]:
def get_cci_data_subset(year, minlon, minlat, maxlon, maxlat):
    url_cci = "https://data.cci.ceda.ac.uk/thredds/dodsC/esacci/biomass/data/agb/maps/v5.01/netcdf/ESACCI-BIOMASS-L4-AGB-MERGED-100m-{}-fv5.01.nc"
    return xr.open_dataset(url_cci.format(year)).sel(lon=slice(minlon, maxlon), lat=slice(maxlat,minlat))

cci_data_list = []
for year in [2010, 2015, 2016]:
    print(year)
    cci_data_list.append(get_cci_data_subset(year, minlon, minlat, maxlon, maxlat))

ds_cci = xr.concat(cci_data_list, dim="time")

Since the OpeNDAP server is unstable, we download the neccessary dataset to disk

fc = ds_cci.agb.plot(col="time", col_wrap=4)
for ax in fc.axs.flatten():
    fire_area.boundary.plot(ax=ax, alpha=0.4, color='r', aspect=None)
fc.fig.suptitle("Biomass annual average", y=1.1)
plt.show()

In [ ]:
ds_cci_diff = ds_cci.agb.diff(dim="time").assign_coords(
    time=[
        "2015-2010",
        "2016-2015",
        "2017-2016",
        "2018-2017",
        "2019-2018",
        "2020-2019",
        "2021-2020",
    ]
).assign_attrs(
    units = ds_cci.agb.attrs["units"],
)
fc = ds_cci_diff.plot(col="time", col_wrap=4)
for ax in fc.axs.flatten():
    fire_area.boundary.plot(ax=ax, alpha=0.4, color='r', aspect=None)
fc.fig.suptitle("Biomass difference between years", y=1.1)
plt.show()
In [ ]:
def clip_raster_from_shape(ds, area_shape):
    ds.rio.set_spatial_dims(x_dim="lon", y_dim="lat", inplace=True)
    ds.rio.write_crs(area_shape.crs, inplace=True)
    da_clipped = ds.rio.clip(
        area_shape.apply(mapping),
        area_shape.crs,
        drop=True,
    )
    return da_clipped

ds_cci_diff_cliped = clip_raster_from_shape(ds_cci_diff, fire_area.geometry)
In [ ]:
ds_cci_diff_cliped.sel(time="2016-2015",).drop_vars("spatial_ref",).rename('agb_change').plot()

In [ ]:
# since the spatial resolution of the CCI dataset is 100m, each grid is 1ha,
# simply summing the values (x 1ha) in the area yields total biomass change Mg (=Ton)
agb_change = ds_cci_diff_cliped.sel(time="2016-2015",).sum(dim=["lat", "lon"]).compute().assign_attrs(
    dict(units="Mg")
)

ratio_root_to_shoot = 0.2232  # Owate et al 2018, BGC/(AGC+BGC)
fraction_carbon_biomass = 0.47  # IPCC 2006
factor_co2_c = 44 / 12

total_biomass_change = agb_change * (1 + ratio_root_to_shoot)
total_carbon_change = total_biomass_change * fraction_carbon_biomass
total_co2eq_change = total_carbon_change * factor_co2_c

print(f"The total loss of CO2eq of Biomass is {total_co2eq_change.values.item()} between 2015 and 2016 in the area of interest.")

The total loss of CO2eq of Biomass is -39828.19921875 between 2015 and 2016 in the area of interest.

European Forest Fire Information System (EFFIS)¶

Burned Area Historical data with live updates. https://forest-fire.emergency.copernicus.eu/applications/data-and-services

There are also other services provides live updates of wildfire alerts. One can subscribe to these services to detect wildfire.
